"Clear yellow-amber pour with a two finger foamy white head with great retention and crazy lacing.  The nose is sweet and citrusy with tons of brown sugar and caramel along with hints of grass, tangerine, and pine.  The taste follows suit with the piney, resiny hops even more prevalent along with sweet caramel malts, brown sugar, orange peel, tangerine, and tropical fruit.  The mouthfeel is thick, chewy, and really oily, with incredible balance and drinkability.  Overall, this is incredibly bold and flavorful, yet totally balanced and drinkable.  I drank the 32 oz. bottle and was left wanting more.  Highly recommended!"
