"Poured a cloudy amber body with one finger of fluffy white head. A very nice looking DIPA, true to style. Scents of pine resin, dank, vegetal, earthy hops, light spicy hops, medium-light notes of orange peel, tangerine, juniper berries and a medium-light presence of alcohol. Overall impression of aroma is of an excellent DIPA that is true to form, very dank and powerful and quite pleasant. Flavor begins with medium-high bitterness with notes of dank, resinous, herbal hops and pine resin, orange peel, medium-light alcohol, and a very light caramel malt backbone. Middle is still bitter, with strong notes of pine resin and resinous hops and bitter, dank, earthy vegetal hops. Finish is bitter with strong notes of pine resin, juniper berries, dank, earthy hops, medium levels of alcohol, orange zest. Aftertaste is pine resin, light alcohol and dank, earthy hops. Overall impression of flavor is of a very bitter, dank, resinous DIPA that is quite nice and very flavorful. Quite nice. Mouthfeel is medium-full bodied with medium carbonation and a drying, resinous feel that starts slick, but finishes drying. Overall impression of mouthfeel is of a nice DIPA that is very easy to drink. Overall this is so good DIPA that has a full aroma and a wonderfully bitter flavor that is resinous, piney and strong. The mouthfeel is the standard feel that aids the experience. A very nice DIPA that is true to form and very nice."
