"Seasonal beers are not normally among my favorites. But this one is a little different. For one thing, brown sugar substitute or not, hints of faux brown sugar are immediately apparent from the first sip. Not too much but it is noticeable. The flavor is a great compliment to the well-blended mix of grains found in this beer. But what really got me was the """holy cow""" moment when I remembered I was drinking an Imperial IPA. My favorite part of this beer is that, as an IPA, it relies on flavors other than hops to set it apart. If you are looking for a super-hoppy pour, this is not your bag. But if you just want a really smooth brew, with very smooth taste, you've found it."
