"Overall (4.25): Lagunitas Sucks is a very good Imperial IPA–it tends towards the resinous/sticky/sweet/fruity route rather than the dry and uber-grapefruity route. I don't have a preference either way; what I can say is that it Lagunitas has executed this kind of Imperial IPA quite well. The only thing that needs to improve is the carbonation level. That's not a huge issue, but it does rob the beer of some of its potential. Still, a very, very tasty beer. Recommended for all those hop heads out there!"
