"This beer pours a nice clearish golden amber color. There is a finger of white head resting on top. The head has good retention, and it leaves a nice sheet of lace behind on the glass. The nose has a nice bit of caramel malt and piney hop presence. There are a good amount of tropical fruit aromas, as well as a nice helping of holiday spices. The taste starts off with a good amount of spice flavor. There is a nice bit of caramel malt and a good amount of piney hop flavor. There is also a bit of fruitiness. The finish leaves some lingering sweetness and hop bitterness behind on the palate. This has a medium body and good carbonation. I goes down easy, and it has a nice smooth feel to it. There is some tingling from the spices and a good amount of hop bitterness. Also, there is some sweetness. A little bit of boozy warmth is noticeable in the finish. this has good drinkability. It is basically holiday IPA which I haven't really experienced before. Overall, I really enjoyed this beer, and I think it is quite unique. I also appreciate Lagunitas sense of humor and commitment to their fans. This is a good beer, and I'm glad I got the chance to try it."
